author: Kelly Cohen
title: Trump: 'Dangerous people' may come to US without immigration order
text:
President Trump expressed concern that without his immigration executive order being enforceable, "bad and dangerous" people may be on their way into the country.
"Because the ban was lifted by a judge, many very bad and dangerous people may be pouring into our country. A terrible decision," the president tweeted Saturday afternoon.
Because the ban was lifted by a judge, many very bad and dangerous people may be pouring into our country. A terrible decisionâ€” Donald J. Trump (@realDonaldTrump) February 4, 2017 
A federal judge in Washington state ruled Friday to halt Trump's executive order banning refugees and immigrants from certain countries. The Trump administration said the Justice Department would be seeking a temporary stay on the ruling.
